sing 'em.<br><br>That tidbit releases you from being shackled to duoing with a healer/shaman for heals.  Those 2 classes will still buff you up nicely though, and the healer in the 40's will get those insta mezzes and stuns and heals that will make your duo insanely deadly against most RvR singles/duos.<br><br>But what would be real fun, from my perspective, would be a nice shadowblade to go out and scout for targets in RvR.  Find one and call in the skald at super speed.  When the orange con thinks he is going to take down the skald, the shadowblade will teach him a lesson from behind.<br><br>I am jealous, the shadowblade would have a dedicated skald to level with...you two should share so you both get a feel for speed and stealth.<br><br>Skald/warrior would rock too...you would not even need heals with the warrior guarding you.<br><br>Hard to resist the mezzes that a healer would bring you though...and you will also find out just how much you hate waiting for power to regen...the healer's power buff really helps there to take the tedium out.<br><br>1) skald/shadowblade (slower leveling, more RvR fun, RvR fun requires patience though)<br>2) skald/healer (buffs make skald uber, healer comes into her own in RvR where you can just rush opponents and use instas)<br>3) skald/warrior <p>-------------------------------------------------------------------<TABLE width=660px><TR><TD width=54%><FONT style="color:blue; font-weight:700; font-size:12">Dark Age Of Camelot, Morgan Le Fay</FONT></TD><TD width=46%><FONT style="color:blue; font-weight:700; font-size:12">Everquest, Mith. Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD><B><FONT font-size:14 color="#CC6600">Leitari (45 Troll Skald Armorer 400 SiegeCraft 4) </TD><TD>Ororo Windrider (58 Gnome Evoker)</TD></TR><TR><TD><FONT color="#66CCFF">JarEd (21 Norse Healer, Aug5 Mend12 Pac15) </TD><TD>Garrett Jax (40 Half-Elf Rogue)</TD></TR><TR><TD><FONT color="#33CC00">Deckan (5 Kobold Rogue Tailor 501) </TD><