 with your mez. But, for overall ability to stay alive and level faster I don't think any combo beats skald/healer. In RvR you are a complete package and starting a group is easy anywhere anytime. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ushortbusdw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShortBusDW</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/5/02 7:17:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> Me and a friend doing a Skald/Berserker combo... never have I leveled so fast.<br><br>Hammer/LA Troll beserker just tears through things.... all I have to do is play rest song.  We actually can manage two reds at the same time when he serks up.<br><br>I like this combo the best. <p><html><body text=#330000 bgcolor=#e5e5c3 link=#330000 vlink=#666666 alink=#999966  ><img src="http://www.darkwolves.org/screenshots/goldwolf.jpg"><BR><a href="http://www.darkwolves.org">www.Darkwolves.org</a></html></body></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uharleybrown.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HarleyBrown</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/5/02 5:06:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I'm with Rosey, Skald/Shaman rocks big time.  Sweet buffs, and heals - with a little offense thrown in.<br><br>Had you asked me a week ago, I would have said berserker purely for the sheer damage output, but a shammy would be the way to go, and what's more, you could both play Trolls.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>mmmmm <p>Bragge (Skald) <BR>Gunreth Doublebarrel (Berserker) <BR>Yelrah Mingunr (Hunter) <BR>Knights of Ni<BR>-------------------------------<BR>Ever dance with the devil in the moonlight?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilgour>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/6/02 9:32:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> My favorite partner is whomever asks.  hehe<br><br>Actually, I enjoy the Skald/SB combination the best.  The damage that a equal level SB does is insane.  i really enjoy the time the two spend together.<br><br>Second, hunter.  Why?  First, no one will party with hunters but with one, you can duo reds.  The damage from the crit makes the diff and the spear styles are phenomenal.<br><br>Third, anyone else, though I put healer/shaman at the top list.  They always need help with leveling and I will never say no to one, even 4 levels below me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bassmf>bassmf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/6/02 12:16:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald / Healer</span><hr size=1> I really like the idea of a skald/shadow for RvR.  But...<br><br>I've played several Midgard combos and from my experience, the skald/healer is the best, and even more so if the shammy is out of the question.  <br><br>Downtime is minimal using the Provoke style and the healer's purity.  The trick to leveling fast is to find high orange/low red mobs and mow through them one at a time.  You will almost never die unless three or more aggro, and even then you will have a chance with your healers insta-heals and insta-mezzing, not to mention your skalds two insta-shouts and one insta-mez (great for quickly pulling aggro off your healer).<br><br>Be sure to get your healer's mend skills up first to get the insta-heals, then work on the pac for the insta-mezzes.  Best MAP (mend/aug/pac) imo is 35/15/38.<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uwarpfield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarpField</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.galia.org/hoodednomads/DAoC/images/emblem/emblem_midgard_thedethguild.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/6/02 1:12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.galia.org/hoodednomads/DAoC/images/emblem/emblem_midgard_thedethguild.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> Its obvious from reading this thread, a Skald works very well with just about everyother class. There are no exceptions IMHO. Each combo will naturally have its advantages and disadvantages but I really can't see that any one is better than another. <br><br>My personal favorites are Skald/Healer, Skald/Shaman. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>__________________________________________<br><ul><li>Muddy Waters - 34 Berzerker</li><br>(Level 376+ Weaponcraft)<br><li>Orobolis - 35 Skald</li><br>(Level 400+ Armorcraft)<li>WarpField Starlighter - 10 Runemaster</li><li>Bitwise Operator - 10 Shaman</li><li>Warpfield - Future Paladin(Nimue, Albion)</li></ul>__________________________________________</b><br><br><img src="http://members.cox.net/mjrsoft/WarpField.jpg"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uzhao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zhao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/7/02 1:37:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I can't speak too well from an RvR perspective, but I can tell you that whenever I've grouped with a healer the killing has been extremely slow and tedious.  No matter how you play the two, you're still sort of gimping your damage output (and if you're trying to minimize downtime you tend to lay off the DD/styles, which doesn't really help at all unless you're fighting easy mobs to start with).  When I'm playing my Skald with a Healer I get bored quickly standing there whacking away at the mob.  I can only imagine how boring it would be for the healer.  Of course some have convinced me that it's fine, but I could never play that role myself.<br><br>If I got to choose a partner I'd go with anything that has decent damage output, like a Shadowblade (left axe), Runemaster, or Berserker, in that order.  (I'm not a huge Thane fan, but admittedly they would make a fine partner too.)  You can plow through mobs pretty quickly this way, and as mentioned earlier your downtime is always relatively short.  Don't underestimate the RM, as the absorb hit line makes a big difference on quick kills later on, and often they can just nuke hard to get you out of a poor situation.<br><br>Those choices are from personal experience.  I'm sure if I had grouped with an equally competent person playing another class I would be recommending it to you.<br><br>Maybe, since a Skald really is so versatile, just let your wife pick a class you think she would like <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Chances are you will make a great duo no matter what. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 11:38:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cableone.net/truggiero/smxumcard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> Anyone ever thought of a Skald/Skald combo? Me and a friend do it daily and we take oranges all day. Can even do reds from time to time. Went from 1 to 24 in a week. Very little downtime if you bounce aggro back and forth. <br><br>I'd definately look at a Skald/Skald or Skald/Zerker combo. Zerkers with Skald Damage add is flat out nasty. <br><br>But the main reason you will want your wife to play a skald as well is so she can have just as much fun as youre going to have. Skalds rock. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A> at: 5/8/02 11:38:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/usylla.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sylla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 12:34:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> Skald/Zerker is an powerful combo. As a duo, there is little worry about &quot;adds&quot;. With the offensive power of the zerker augmented by damage add, you can easily hunt reds. <br><br>On the subject of RvR groups, has anyone grouped with hunters? I have yet to try it but I think the combo of a skald and a couple of hunters would make a great strike team. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udaocobserver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DAoC Observer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 6:58:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> What great advice...thanks, everyone! So far my wife and I have leveled a Skald and a Healer up to 12, and...um...it's sure a lot more pleasant than leveling a Hibernian Druid/Champion team. A lot a lot. Seriously, what's UP with Hibernia? It coulda been so cool, and instead it's an endless golf course. And the melee fighters (Spear Heroes excepted) are about as scary as caddies.<br><br>Still, I'm thinking about bringing a Berserker up to 12, just to give the ol' infinite-damage combo a try, and maybe taking a Dark-spec Spiritmaster out for a ramble too. So any further stories of your experiences with Skald duoing would be well-appreciated.<br><br>Love these boards!<br><br>- Corvus Sable, 12 Norse Skald, Nimue<br><br>(Yeah, I know Midgard's already kicking butt on Nimue, but it was the last RP server I hadn't used already) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=etzel>Etzel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 3:48:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> A healer is fun for a while but having played one to early 30's it gets old real quick. The little things annoy you, having to be permanently anon once you pass lvl10, fully buffing up in a dungeon get a bad add, run out and you're back to buffing again, always having to stand back in RvR watching others deal damage. I'm not saying your pair is bad but know the pitfalls before you expend too much time on one or the other, maybe you can alternate chars so that you both get to deal damage?<br><br>On the positive side I say zerker or SB, if you are sure you'll be duoing 99% of the time i'd go SB with a full axe/left axe/poison template (skipping CS/Stealth because by default you'd need to be apart a lot of the time). If you intend to solo a little go 5 spec. Of course the quote that always sticks in my mind regarding skald/zerk combo is that 'the skald is the guided missile, the zerker the payload'....... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvalcurtain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valcurtain</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thelostempire.net/images/TinyCrux.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 12:11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I agree with the Skald/Shaman combo. . .a couple DOTs on the mob make them die faster, buffs are a boon, and the heals during down time are great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/upiechow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>piechow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/10/02 1:36:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=40.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best duo partner for a Skald?</span><hr size=1> I like skald/shammy combo, since I use 2 computers it works out well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>